            "body": "> Sometimes we have created non-focusable decoration windows on top of the current non-float window and rather don't want to obscure the cursor.\n\nInstead of a new flag, why don't we just make a decision that always applies?\n\n- Unfocusable windows don't \"cover\" the cursor and don't cause an \"empty\" cursor-shape.\n    - This could include \"pinned\" windows: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/36130",
